article.headline: George Mason 76, East Carolina 65
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. (AP)-- Raoul Heinen had career-highs of 23 points and 10 rebounds to lead George Mason to a 76-65 victory over East Carolina on Tuesday night, ending the Pirates' three-game winning streak. Heinen shot 9-for-14, including 5-for-7 from 3-point range, and had four assists and a steal. Lamar Butler scored 16 points for the Patriots (3-1), including three consecutive 3-pointers that blew the game open in the second half. Belton Rivers led East Carolina (3-1) with 13 points. Erroyl Bing added 11 points and 14 rebounds. Rivers' back-to-back 3-pointers gave the Pirates a 56-49 lead midway through the first half. Butler answered with three 3-pointers to spark a 17-0 run for George Mason, giving the patriots a 66-56 lead with 4:19 left. The Pirates failed to make another field goal until the final minute. <
